{"tid":1852864,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"個個講肺炎, 無人記得今日英國行出脫歐第一步","createTime":"2020-01-30T15:55:07.000Z","updateTime":"2020-01-30T16:33:37.000Z","uid":130105,"like":2,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":4,"replies":[{"pid":"6558bf5147cf067bd623b6a5b28cdacc0a8ff9bb","tid":1852864,"uid":130105,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-30T15:55:07.000Z","msg":"冇人記得<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/think.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/think.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n===================================<br />\n&bull;Brexit formally set for 11pm on Friday as UK politicians start packing their bags <br />\n&bull;Nigel Farage's office was full of boxes and mementos to be packed and shipped<br />\n&bull;On Wednesday EU parliament should overwhelmingly approve Brexit withdrawal<br />\n&bull;Farage's favourite souvenir is framed Economist cover with him Trump and Putin<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24010588-7939611-image-a-63_1580259640207.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24010588-7939611-image-a-63_1580259640207.jpg&h=f964dd8a&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Brexit Party leader Nigel Farage packs his items in his office at the European Parliament in Brussels, Belgium, on Tuesday<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24010592-7939611-image-a-65_1580261104332.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24010592-7939611-image-a-65_1580261104332.jpg&h=7eaddb9e&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Farage packs his items in his office in Brussels, including paintings and souvenirs from his long career in the European Parliament<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24010584-7939611-image-a-66_1580261111484.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24010584-7939611-image-a-66_1580261111484.jpg&h=b71af73b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Brexit Party leader Nigel Farage in his office at the European Parliament in Brussels as British MEPs began clearing their offices ahead of Brexit<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24012052-7939611-image-a-68_1580261890002.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24012052-7939611-image-a-68_1580261890002.jpg&h=c0abb83d&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Personal items on a desk in Nigel Farage's office including a cartoon depicting the Brexit Party leader at the European Parliament in Brussels<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/23994810-7939611-Nigel_Farage_has_started_removing_personal_items_from_his_Brusse-a-64_1580261093075.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F23994810-7939611-Nigel_Farage_has_started_removing_personal_items_from_his_Brusse-a-64_1580261093075.jpg&h=b7fa4581&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Nigel Farage has started removing personal items from his Brussels office. During his 20-year career as an MEP, he had long campaigned for Britain to leave the EU<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24010614-7939611-image-a-67_1580261132369.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24010614-7939611-image-a-67_1580261132369.jpg&h=0566150b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Nigel Farage wore Union flag socks ready for Wednesday's plenary when the EU parliament should overwhelmingly approve the Brexit withdrawal agreement<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/00/23993878-7939509-British_European_Parliament_member_and_leader_of_Labour_Party_de-a-112_1580258284827.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F00%2F23993878-7939509-British_European_Parliament_member_and_leader_of_Labour_Party_de-a-112_1580258284827.jpg&h=ce2e838d&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n British European Parliament member and leader of Labour Party delegation Richard Corbett holding a scarf as he packs some of his belongings at his office at the European Parliament in Brussels on Monday<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/28/18/wire-23993842-1580236793-928_634x422.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F28%2F18%2Fwire-23993842-1580236793-928_634x422.jpg&h=56dcd205&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n British European Parliament member of the Group of the Progressive Alliance of Socialists and Democrats Judith Kirton-Darling packing some of her belongings at her office in Brussels on Monday<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24012034-7939611-image-a-69_1580261932884.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24012034-7939611-image-a-69_1580261932884.jpg&h=bbbbc050&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Britain's Green party MEP Magid Magid packing up his office at the European Parliament in Brussels this week<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24011502-7939611-image-a-70_1580261939546.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24011502-7939611-image-a-70_1580261939546.jpg&h=27e1115f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Britain's Brexit Party MEP Claire Fox is one of 72 other UK MEPs leaving Brussels this week<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/24012480-7939611-image-a-71_1580262912287.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F24012480-7939611-image-a-71_1580262912287.jpg&h=705e0c85&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Greens/EFA party members of European Parliament holding a banner, as they take part in a symbolic demonstration to mark the departure of the UK from the EU in front of the European Parliament on Tuesday<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/01/29/01/23993924-7939611-People_walking_down_a_main_avenue_in_the_EU_Quarter_of_Brussels_-m-72_1580262951682.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2020%2F01%2F29%2F01%2F23993924-7939611-People_walking_down_a_main_avenue_in_the_EU_Quarter_of_Brussels_-m-72_1580262951682.jpg&h=c79b1848&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n People walking down a main avenue in the EU Quarter of Brussels. The UK is due to leave the EU on Friday, the first nation in the bloc to do so<br />\n<br />\nsource:<a href=\"https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-7939611/With-joy-sadness-UK-MEPs-pack-Brussels.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticle-7939611%2FWith-joy-sadness-UK-MEPs-pack-Brussels.html&d=kJJ5Rp8RNWWpGPQirZinA%2Fhh9XvCW3eHRhDz%2B7Q%2FvTo%3D&h=07e9b9c6\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-7939611/With-joy-sadness-UK-MEPs-pack-Brussels.html</a>"},{"pid":"0a40954b20ba428149f4f946ab0778e64677080d","tid":1852864,"uid":176447,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-30T15:56:55.000Z","msg":"WFC<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"aae1fcd3db6c4a9348974b4a10e7f67bec70292d","tid":1852864,"uid":60545,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-30T16:00:22.000Z","msg":"冇人想知英國點<img src=\"/assets/faces/lny/smile3.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n叫佢地用支為用得開心啲啦"},{"pid":"41357dba3509d194efbc3d29ea8e7dd6cefe8c07","tid":1852864,"uid":48973,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-30T16:07:47.000Z","msg":"日已落帝國<br />\n<br />\nwfc"},{"pid":"314aef3bbf3af504187cfc2cb5ca2cd7f01a2dcf","tid":1852864,"uid":130105,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":